fu.util

Class DoubleSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • fu.util.DoubleSet

  • public class DoubleSet
extends java.lang.Object
    A list of double that supports union, intersect, subtract. The main idea: set elements are simply added in any order, but if a set method is to be computed, the sets are sorted in order to speed up method execution.

      • remove

        public boolean remove(double number)
        Removes a value from the set. It is only removed if the value in the set occurs identical. If the value does not occur, the set remained unchanged (in particular, no exception is triggered). The caller can check the return value (true: the value was in the set and removed, false: the value was not in the set).
        Parameters:
        number - number to remove
        Returns:
        true, if the number was in the set
